      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Research generally shows that \"tough on crime\" policies have little to no impact on overall crime rates but do make communities safer for rich neighborhoods at the expense of low-income ones. These approaches often lead to mass incarceration and disproportionate harm for Black and Brown Americans without actually reducing violence or addressing its root causes. Ultimately, true public safety requires investing in social services and community rehabilitation rather than merely increasing penalties.",
